.TH BUTLER 1 "2026-06-12" "butler 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
butler \- command\-line client for the BuchhaltungsButler (BHB) accounting API
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B butler
.I resource verb
.RI [ flags ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B butler
is a small, dependency\-free client for the BuchhaltungsButler accounting
API. It lists, searches and books entries from the terminal using an
AWS/\fBgh\fR\-style
.I "resource verb"
grammar. Output is an aligned table by default, or raw JSON with
.B \-\-output json
for piping into \fBjq\fR.
.SH RESOURCES
.TP
.B transactions
bank transactions (list, show)
.TP
.B receipts
receipts / documents (list, show, upload, delete)
.TP
.B postings
extended bookings (list, create, unconfirm), alias: bookings
.TP
.B accounts
chart of accounts (list)
.TP
.B status
test API connectivity and show client info
.TP
.B login
store credentials for a profile
.TP
.B logout
explain how to remove a profile's credentials
.SH COMMANDS
.SS butler transactions list [flags]
.TP
.B \-\-date\-from YYYY\-MM\-DD
earliest booking date
.TP
.B \-\-date\-to YYYY\-MM\-DD
latest booking date
.TP
.B \-\-account n
bank account number
.TP
.B \-\-to\-from text
counterparty filter (server\-side)
.TP
.B \-\-id\-from n
lowest id (exclusive)
.TP
.B \-\-id\-to n
highest id (exclusive)
.TP
.B \-\-filter text
case\-insensitive substring over the shown columns
.TP
.B \-\-limit n
max rows
.TP
.B \-\-offset n
skip the first n rows
.SS butler transactions show <id>
.TP
.B id
transaction id_by_customer
.PP
Show a single transaction by its id_by_customer.
.br
.SS butler receipts list <inbound|outbound> [flags]
.TP
.B inbound|outbound
receipt direction (required)
.TP
.B \-\-counterparty text
counterparty filter
.TP
.B \-\-date\-from YYYY\-MM\-DD
earliest date
.TP
.B \-\-date\-to YYYY\-MM\-DD
latest date
.TP
.B \-\-payment\-status s
e.g. paid | unpaid
.TP
.B \-\-invoice\-number s
invoice number filter
.TP
.B \-\-due\-date YYYY\-MM\-DD
due\-date filter
.TP
.B \-\-include\-offers
include offers
.TP
.B \-\-deleted
include deleted receipts
.TP
.B \-\-filter text
case\-insensitive substring over the shown columns
.TP
.B \-\-limit n
max rows
.TP
.B \-\-offset n
skip the first n rows
.SS butler receipts show <id> [\-\-direction inbound|outbound]
.TP
.B id
receipt id_by_customer
.TP
.B \-\-direction inbound|outbound
narrow the lookup
.br
values: inbound, outbound
.PP
Show a single receipt by its id_by_customer.
.br
.PP
BHB's get\-by\-id route returns HTTP 404 (server\-side bug), so butler looks
.br
the id up via the list endpoint; at most 500 receipts per direction are
.br
searched. Pass \-\-direction to narrow the lookup.
.br
.SS butler receipts upload <file> \-\-type <type> [flags]
.TP
.B file
path to the receipt file
.TP
.B \-\-type type
receipt type, e.g. "invoice inbound" (required)
.TP
.B \-\-counterparty text
counterparty
.TP
.B \-\-invoice\-number s
invoice number
.TP
.B \-\-date YYYY\-MM\-DD
document date
.TP
.B \-\-amount n
gross amount
.TP
.B \-\-vat\-rate n
vat rate
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
print what would be sent, send nothing
.SS butler receipts delete <id>
.TP
.B id
receipt id_by_customer
.PP
Delete a receipt by its id_by_customer.
.br
.SS butler postings list \-\-date\-from D \-\-date\-to D [flags]
.TP
.B \-\-date\-from YYYY\-MM\-DD
earliest date (required)
.TP
.B \-\-date\-to YYYY\-MM\-DD
latest date (required)
.TP
.B \-\-account csv
accounts filter (e.g. "free booking")
.TP
.B \-\-postingaccount csv
posting\-account filter (e.g. 3790)
.TP
.B \-\-status s
all | fixed | unfixed
.TP
.B \-\-order s
e.g. "date ASC"
.TP
.B \-\-cost\-location s
cost location filter
.TP
.B \-\-filter text
case\-insensitive substring over the shown columns
.TP
.B \-\-limit n
max rows
.TP
.B \-\-offset n
skip the first n rows
.SS butler postings create (\-\-from\-json <file> | <line flags>) [flags]
.TP
.B \-\-from\-json file
JSON array of split lines (see FORMAT)
.TP
.B \-\-date YYYY\-MM\-DD
single line: date
.TP
.B \-\-debit acct
single line: debit account
.TP
.B \-\-credit acct
single line: credit account
.TP
.B \-\-amount n
single line: positive amount, e.g. 5000.00
.TP
.B \-\-vat code
single line: vat code
.br
values: 0_none, 19_vat, 7_vat, 19_pre, 7_pre, 19_both_1, 19_both_2, 7_both, 19_both_1_no_pre, 19_both_2_no_pre, 7_both_no_pre, 19_pre_app, 7_pre_app, 19_both_app_1, 19_both_app_2, 7_both_app
.TP
.B \-\-text s
single line: posting text
.TP
.B \-\-cost\-location s
optional cost location
.TP
.B \-\-clearing acct
assert this account nets to zero before sending
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
print the redacted payload, send nothing
.PP
New postings are created CONFIRMED (visible to the API and the web UI,
.br
still unfixed so they stay editable/deletable in the UI). To stage one
.br
for UI\-only review, unconfirm it afterwards: butler postings unconfirm <id>.
.br
.PP
\-\-from\-json FORMAT
.br
  [ {"date":"2026\-05\-31","postingtext":"...","amount":"5000.00",
.br
     "debit":6020,"credit":3790,"vat":"0_none"} , ... ]
.br
.SS butler postings unconfirm <id>
.TP
.B id
posting id
.PP
Set a free posting back to unconfirmed by its posting id.
.br
.SS butler postings delete [id]
.TP
.B id
posting id (unused — deletion is web\-UI only)
.PP
The BHB API has no posting\-delete endpoint; this command only explains
.br
that deletion must happen in the web UI, and exits with a usage error.
.br
.SS butler accounts list [flags]
.TP
.B \-\-filter text
case\-insensitive substring over the shown columns
.TP
.B \-\-limit n
max rows
.TP
.B \-\-offset n
skip the first n rows
.SS status
Probe the BHB API (authenticated) and print the api base, profile, and butler/API
.br
versions. Exits non\-zero if the call fails.
.br
.SS login
Prompt for api_client / api_secret / api_key and store them in
.br
$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/butler/credentials (default ~/.config/butler/credentials),
.br
mode 0600.
.br
.SS logout
Explains how to remove a profile's [section] from the credentials file
.br
($XDG_CONFIG_HOME/butler/credentials, default ~/.config/butler/credentials).
.br
.SH GLOBAL FLAGS
.TP
.B \-\-profile name
credentials profile (default: default)
.TP
.B \-\-output table|json
output format (default: table)
.br
values: table, json
.TP
.B \-\-api\-base url
override API base URL (https unless \-\-insecure)
.TP
.B \-\-debug
print the request line to stderr
.TP
.B \-\-insecure
allow sending credentials over a non\-HTTPS api\-base
.TP
.B \-\-help
show help; per command: `<resource> <verb> \-\-help`
.TP
.B \-\-version
print the butler version
.SH AUTHENTICATION
butler needs an API client id, an API client secret (HTTP Basic auth) and
an account api_key (sent in each request body). Store them with
.B butler login
or via the
.BR BUTLER_API_CLIENT ", " BUTLER_API_SECRET " and " BUTLER_API_KEY
environment variables (which take precedence over the file).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/butler/credentials
INI file of profiles, mode 0600 (honours \fB$XDG_CONFIG_HOME\fR).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
success
.TP
.B 1
API or HTTP error
.TP
.B 2
usage error
.SH SEE ALSO
Full reference and examples: the project README and docs/commands.md.
.SH AUTHOR
An independent, unofficial client; not affiliated with BuchhaltungsButler GmbH.
